# Tailwind UI & dashboards

When designing or changing **any page layout, dashboard, or overview**:

1. **Check Tailwind UI / Tailwind Plus first**
   - **Bento grids:** https://tailwindcss.com/plus/ui-blocks/marketing/sections/bento-grids  
     Use bento-style card grids (varied cell sizes, rounded corners, clear hierarchy).
   - **Application UI:** https://tailwindcss.com/plus/ui-blocks/application-ui  
     Tables, feeds, form layouts, navbars.
   - **UI Blocks index:** https://tailwindcss.com/plus/ui-blocks  

2. **Dashboard layout**
   - Prefer a **bento grid**: mix of compact KPI/summary cards and larger content cards.
   - Use semantic spacing: `gap-4` / `gap-6`, `rounded-2xl`, **shadow** (`shadow-sm`), and **background contrast** (`bg-muted/20`, `bg-background`). **NEVER use borders** (no `border`, no `ring` as outline) â€” see AGENTS.md 4.0.
   - Use theme tokens: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-muted/30`.
   - Avoid long single-column dumps; use grids with `grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4` or asymmetric `col-span-2` for visual interest.

3. **AGENTS.md** (section 4.1) has the full guideline; this rule is a reminder to always look at Tailwind UI for inspiration before implementing.
